node.accessibility_caption: 2 brewers stand in front of a 15bbl stainless steel brewhouse

node.text:
Our next Black Barn Program beer is in the tanks! ⁣
⁣
This week we brewed Black Barn Program No. 24 Kölsch style ale. This 5% ode to Cologne Germany’s answer to the lager, is a Black Barn Program recipe by our packaging team member Abby. Brewed with Cashmere and Hallertau Mittelfrüh hops this is the perfect summer quencher! ⁣
⁣
We will be releasing Black Barn Program No. 24 in bottles and on draft exclusively from our tasting room Monday August 16th at 11am.

node.accessibility_caption: 2 brewers stand in front of a 15bbl stainless steel brewhouse
The label for Black Barn Program No 24
A bottle of Dinner and a Dinner glass lie on a piece of train track with rocks on either side.

node.text: Don’t worry your glass of Dinner won’t be empty for long, we have a fresh batch releasing from the tasting room this Friday July 30th at 11am!

node.accessibility_caption: An overhead view of Little Whaleboat islands and ledges

node.text:
We are excited to announce today that as part of our @1percentftp commitment, we are working with our partners at @maine_coast_heritage_trust to help preserve a cluster of 3 small undeveloped islands and ledges in Casco Bay. ⁣
⁣
Known as The Little Whaleboat Island Project, these islands (Little Whaleboat, Tuck, & Nate) are a vital link in the chain of protected islands off Harpswell already conserved by MCHt. If successful, the project will guarantee permanent public access, provide sanctuary to a range of wildlife, including seals, seabirds, shorebirds, and wading birds, and secure an overnight campsite that is currently on the @meislandtrail .⁣
⁣
Our $50,000 gift has been matched dollar for dollar by anonymous donors, we're asking our followers to join in to help raise the remaining $400,000 MCHT needs to purchase the island by December 31st. Go to the link in our bio to donate and any contribution large or small will be matched.
⁣
Join us in helping to protect these incredible islands for future generations to enjoy! (📷 @jerrymonkman )

node.accessibility_caption: An overhead view of Little Whaleboat islands and ledges
3 people sit around a beach campfire on the island with Maine Beer Company beer.
A chart map of Little Whaleboat island

node.text: Perfect pairing for a campfire night🏕

node.accessibility_caption: A bottle of Another One IPA sits in a sunbeam in the woods with a gray speckled Maine Beer Company camp mug.

node.text: Kicking off another beautiful weekend here in Freeport!

node.accessibility_caption: A bottle of Lunch sits atop 3 Black Sabbath albums.

node.text: We’re brewing Lunch batch #666 today, so we have some classic metal lined up for the turntable.

node.accessibility_caption: A grey with white speckles Maine Beer Company camp mug sits on a log covered with mushrooms.

node.text:
Nothing like a post rain hike to get a shot of our new camp cup! ⁣
⁣
Available at the tasting room and our online webstore, they’re perfect for keeping your beer cold or your coffee warm.

node.accessibility_caption: A bottle and snifter of a tiny beautiful something sit in front of the roadside Maine Beer Company sign that advertises fresh beer and wood fired pizza.

node.text:
a tiny beautiful something, our pale ale brewed exclusively with El Dorado hops, is back in bottles and on draft in our tasting room and heading out to distribution this week!⁣
⁣
With notes of orange marmalade, apricot and spice, this is one of our favorite beers to pair with food: think ceviche, salads with citrus, chèvre, and even dessert.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maine Beer Company in Primo Restaurant with @primorestaurant. May be an image of drink.

node.text: Can’t make a trip to the midcoast without getting a little Lunch for dinner.

node.accessibility_caption: The entrance to a barn dinner with lights strung through the rafters.

node.text:
Thank you to @wolfesneckcenter and @chavalmaine for a wonderful farm to table dinner last night at the Mallett Barn. Over 90% of the meal prepared by @chavalmaine was from our state, and included fruit, meat, and vegetables from Wolfe's Neck Farm as well as local cheese from @winterhillfarmer , cocktails from @nedistilling , and of course @mainebeerco beer.⁣
⁣
These dinners are a great reminder of the importance of sourcing local, and the role we play in supporting the farmers and businesses in our community.

node.text:
Wherever adventure takes you this weekend from the wilderness, to local parks, even your own back yard, make sure you follow the 7 Principles of @leavenotracecenter to minimize your impact on the outdoors. ⁣
⁣
-Plan ahead and prepare.⁣
-Travel and camp on durable surfaces.⁣
-Dispose of waste properly.⁣
-Leave what you find. ⁣
-Minimize campfire impacts.⁣
-Respect wildlife.⁣
-Be considerate of other visitors. ⁣
⁣
On our travels to Maine’s islands we always bring a bag to pack out anything we have brought with us to make sure we leave things as we found them for the next visitors to experience. ⁣
⁣
